description.narrative: UNICEF has contributed to solid achievements in advancing adolescent health services including sustaining uptake of reproductive health services through the UNICEF-supported Teen Hub and improving life skills among adolescent girls living with HIV and adolescent mothers. Fourty-four health facilities are implementing adolescent-friendly service standards and the Teen hub served more than 6,500 adolescent boys and girls. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:05/02/2020
